INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (299, 1, '2013-09-22 18:26:57', '2013-09-22 18:26:57', '<blockquote><strong>Software solutions in batch scanning, archiving and viewing of SAP documents and the exchange of SAP documents and data with other information systems contribute significantly to the faster execution of business operations, greater transparency of documentation and business, and consequently to better efficiency. What follows is a description of the examples of solutions that have been created in view of the most common requirements and needs of SAP users.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<div><a title="Internal scanning and archiving of received documents" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/solution-for-sap/internal-scanning-and-archiving-of-received-documents/">INTERNAL SCANNING AND ARCHIVING OF RECEIVED DOCUMENTS</a>\r\nThe documents received are equipped with bar codes and batch scanned. During automatic routing, the scanned documents (objects) are assigned an ID while being stored in the IMiS®/ARChive Server; data from the bar codes, metadata and the IDs of saved objects are stored in the SAP record. A connection is established between the archived object and the SAP record via the ArchiveLink interface. When users open a SAP document, they can view the scanned documents that are stored on the archive server, independent of the SAP system, by clicking on the attachment.\r\n\r\n<a title="External scanning and archiving of received documents" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/solution-for-sap/external-scanning-and-archiving-of-received-documents/">EXTERNAL SCANNING AND ARCHIVING OF RECEIVED DOCUMENTS\r\n</a>The provider of scanning services delivers the files of scanned documents and the index files containing the metadata. During automatic routing, the scanned documents (objects) are assigned an ID while being stored in the IMiS®/ARChive Server; data from the index file and the IDs of saved objects are stored in the SAP record. A connection is established between the archived object and the SAP record via the ArchiveLink interface.\r\n\r\n<a title="Archiving of outgoing documents" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/solution-for-sap/archiving-of-outgoing-documents/">ARCHIVING OF OUTGOING DOCUMENTS\r\n</a>Archiving of outgoing documents is carried out automatically via a standardized ArchiveLink interface for archiving outgoing documents. The mode of archiving outgoing documents is determined exclusively by configuring the SAP system.\r\n\r\n<a title="Archiving of received digitally signed documents" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/solution-for-sap/archiving-of-received-digitally-signed-documents/">ARCHIVING OF RECEIVED DIGITALLY SIGNED DOCUMENTS\r\n</a>Archiving of received digitally signed documents is sensible in order to ensure the authenticity and unified register of all documents. Outgoing SAP documents are printed with bar codes, which are uniquely determined by the types and numbers of the documents. The received digitally signed documents are batch scanned as incoming documents and archived in the IMiS®/ARChive Server electronic archive.\r\n\r\n<a title="Access to archived sap objects for users of other systems" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/solution-for-sap/access-to-archived-sap-objects-for-users-of-other-systems/">ACCESS TO ARCHIVED SAP OBJECTS FOR USERS OF OTHER SYSTEM\r\n</a>Access to archived SAP objects for users of other systems enables authorized users to search through several, preset metadata and display results according to the defined dependency of SAP documents, in accordance with the security scheme.\r\n\r\n<a title="The document management system and the sap system complement each other" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/solution-for-sap/the-document-management-system-and-the-sap-system-complement-each-other/">THE DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT SYSTEM AND THE SAP SYSTEM COMPLEMENT EACH OTHER\r\n</a><span style="color: #333333;">The document management system and the SAP system complement each other. They are linked in order to achieve automated data exchange between the two systems, a higher automation level and better efficiency.<a title="The document management system and the sap system complement each other" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/solution-for-sap/the-document-management-system-and-the-sap-system-complement-each-other/">\r\n\r\n</a></span><a title="The security of electronically archived sap documents" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/solution-for-sap/the-security-of-electronically-archived-sap-documents/">THE SECURITY OF ELECTRONICALLY ARCHIVED SAP DOCUMENTS\r\n</a>The security of electronically archived SAP documents is ensured by state-of-the-art AES-256 algorithms for encrypting.</div>', 'Solution for SAP', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'solution-for-sap', '', '', '2013-10-16 19:30:38', '2013-10-16 19:30:38', '', 296, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=299', 3, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (300, 1, '2013-09-22 18:26:57', '2013-09-22 18:26:57', '', 'Solution for SAP', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '299-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:26:57', '2013-09-22 18:26:57', '', 299, 'http://imis.eberce.si/299-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (302, 1, '2013-09-22 18:27:28', '2013-09-22 18:27:28', '<blockquote><strong>The document management system enables effective management of paper documentation, a faster and higher quality flow of information, greater control over the implementation of processes, better insight into the cost effectiveness of business operations, the interconnection of information sources and conformity with the regulations in force. With the electronic implementation of document-intensive processes in a document management system, the processes are carried out significantly faster. Searching for documents is quick and easy; documents are not misplaced or lost; processing takes place faster. Employees can devote more of their attention to customers and value-added tasks and less to administration. </strong>\r\n<strong>By meeting the demands of customers more quickly, we are improving the level of services. Greater knowledge of the implementation of processes enables faster business decision-making.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Below is a list of the important features that we believe a <a title="Document management systems" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/document-management-systems/"><strong>DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT</strong></a> should offer:\r\n\r\nIndividual and batch scanning enables a fast capture of documents that are immediately archived and thus made available to authorized users for the implementation of work processes.\r\n\r\nThe authenticity of electronic documents is confirmed by an electronic signature, which guarantees the authenticity of the document and the signee, the unalterability of the signed content and enables the determining of the origin of the signed content.\r\n\r\nData and documents from different sources are automatically routed to the document management system, which saves time on entering the record data and achieves greater transparency of the documents.\r\n\r\nElectronic support for processes (workflow) enables the optimization of working with documents, faster and greater access, a simple and organized method of working with business documentation, effective control over the implementation of business processes, precise tracking of work carried out, etc.\r\n\r\nOptical character recognition (OCR) of scanned documents is performed for all documents in full, thus ensuring a search through the full text of the documents. We can quickly find random parts of the text in documents, thus improving work productivity. We also save valuable time in the event of having to re-enter the text of received documents (retyping).\r\n\r\nThe existence of documents at a certain moment in time and their unalterability is confirmed with timestamping.\r\n\r\nSecure storing of a large number of objects, reliable operation, quick and easy search for objects and the option of storing them separately from applications are the key advantages of using an electronic document archive.\r\n\r\nFor the needs of mutual data exchange the document management system can be connected to other systems and applications.\r\n\r\nThe tool for process and data analysis is used to determine bottlenecks in the process and consequently optimize the implementation of the process. In order for its operation to be more responsive, the views and analyses are performed outside the document management system. Quality control over the implementation of processes can be a good foundation for the establishment of a more effective remuneration model.</div>\r\n</div>', 'Document management systems', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'document-management-systems', '', '', '2013-10-17 21:09:34', '2013-10-17 21:09:34', '', 296, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=302', 1, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (303, 1, '2013-09-22 18:27:28', '2013-09-22 18:27:28', '', 'Document management systems', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:27:28', '2013-09-22 18:27:28', '', 302, 'http://imis.eberce.si/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (304, 1, '2013-09-22 18:27:53', '2013-09-22 18:27:53', '<blockquote><strong>IMiS®/ARChive Server is a safe, reliable and scalable archive system, intended for storing objects (of electronic source or digitized via the scanning process). Objects are stored in the structure of archive profiles. The archive system architecture is flexible and enables the setting up of a larger number of archive servers and the establishment of various roles in a hierarchy.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Speed of operation (responsiveness, forwarding of archived objects) is independent of the archive size.The security of archived objects is provided with a unique, 256-bit encrypted identifier (ID), which is assigned to each archived object during the storage phase.In environments where security is not provided by infrastructure (internet connections or exchange of highly delicate information), the internationally used and recognized AES-256 encryption standard is used to encrypt traffic between the server and the clients.For the needs of storing objects separately from the application, the archive server is connected to various applications (DMS, ERP, CMS). For the application to access IMiS<sup>®</sup>/ARChive Server we use IMiS<sup>®</sup> clients (IMiS<sup>®</sup>/Scan, IMiS<sup>®</sup>/View) or the IMiS<sup>®</sup>/Storage Connector server.The application''s security scheme defines the users that can access and view archived objects.\r\n\r\nThe audit trail, in accordance with the requirements of the legislation (Protection of Documents and Archives and Archival Institutions Act - ZVDAGA/ETZ), records all data on the implementation of operations on archived objects and is accessible only to users with special rights.\r\n\r\nThe high availability of the IMiS®/ARChive Server archive system is achieved by switching to replication and a fail-over location, thus setting up a secondary archive system in a remote location.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Electronic archive', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'electronic-archive', '', '', '2013-10-17 20:22:55', '2013-10-17 20:22:55', '', 296, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=304', 2, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (305, 1, '2013-09-22 18:27:53', '2013-09-22 18:27:53', '', 'Electronic Archive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '304-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:27:53', '2013-09-22 18:27:53', '', 304, 'http://imis.eberce.si/304-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (306, 1, '2013-09-22 18:28:59', '2013-09-22 18:28:59', '<blockquote><strong>The IMiS software product consists of modules for scanning, archiving, reviewing, routing, optical recognition, forwarding of and searching for documents, and application integration. They are easy to use and logically interconnected.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>IMiS/Scan is used for scanning documents, reviewing and electronically signing them. The scanned documents, together with other types of files, are stored on IMiS/ARChive Server and searched by metadata.The scanned documents are reviewed and electronically signed with IMiS/View.\r\n\r\nIMiS/BatchScan is intended for scanning a larger number of paper documents.\r\nBatch scanning creates documents that are stored on IMiS/ARChive Server by IMiS/Avalanche and appropriately routed to applications on the basis of bar codes and metadata.\r\n\r\nIMiS/StorageConnector transfers scanned documents and files between applications and the IMiS/ARChive Server electronic archive.\r\n\r\nIMiS/OCR Server recognizes the characters of the text of scanned documents, thus enabling the full text search of documents in the IBM Lotus Domino/Notes applications.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'IMiS modules', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'imis-modules', '', '', '2013-10-16 20:26:37', '2013-10-16 20:26:37', '', 0, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=306', 2, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (307, 1, '2013-09-22 18:28:59', '2013-09-22 18:28:59', '', 'IMiS modules', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '306-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:28:59', '2013-09-22 18:28:59', '', 306, 'http://imis.eberce.si/306-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (308, 1, '2013-09-22 18:30:00', '2013-09-22 18:30:00', '<blockquote><strong>During optical character recognition, IMiS/OCR Server converts scanned documents into text. It recognizes the characters of a majority of world languages. It can be used as a mail-in service, in which we receive the recognized text by e-mail, or in the IBM Lotus Notes/Domino environment, where it converts the recognized text into one of the selected formats and builds a Full Text Search (FTS) index for the needs of searching through the entire text.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Better Efficiency</span>\r\nScanned documents stored to an electronic archive provide fast and simple access to documents which we would otherwise look for in file cabinets and folders.\r\nEfficiency can be additionally improved by the option of fast searching for parts of text, set phrases, keywords in scanned documents (contract clauses, letter content, etc.), knowledge bases, etc., which is enabled by IMiS/OCR Server.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Use of text from Received Documents</span>\r\nWe often wish to use part of a text or the whole text from certain received documents. Retyping or re-entering such text is time-consuming and unproductive.\r\nIn this case, we first scan the documents, select the language and output format of the recognized text and send an e-mail with an attached scanned document to be recognized to IMiS/OCR Server.\r\nImmediately after processing, IMiS/OCR Server sends back another e-mail with the recognized text in one of the selected formats (DOCX, DOC, RTF, XLSX, XLS, TXT, PPTX, PDF/A, etc.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Long-Term Storage of Documents in TIFF and PDF/A Format</span>\r\nDocuments intended for long-term storage in the electronic archive must be ensured readability and authenticity even after 5, 10 or more years. Suitable formats for\r\nlong-term storage are TIFF and PDF/A. Other graphic formats of documents can be converted into the PDF/A format by IMiS/OCR Server.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Use in the IBM Lotus Notes/Domino Environment</span>\r\nFor the needs of full text search (FTS) IMiS/OCR Server controls the entry of new scanned documents into one or several databases and converts them into the PDF/A format during optical character recognition. It then enters the textual representation of the recognition into a Lotus Notes document, making it possible for the Domino server to build an index across the whole text, thus enabling FTS.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Support for Structure Oriented Architecture (SOA)</span>\r\nThe IMiS/OCR Server interface complies with the accepted SOA standards, which ensures a high level of interoperability with various information systems.\r\nThe open interface is easy to use, and at the same time offers the option of affecting any level in the process of optical character recognition and conversion of scanned documents to complex information systems. Because of SOA, the use of the IMiS/OCR Server module is not limited to only one technological platform; on the contrary,\r\noptical character recognition and FTS indexing can be used in all modern service-oriented applications that enable FTS.', 'IMiS/OCR Server', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'imisocr-server', '', '', '2013-10-16 20:20:40', '2013-10-16 20:20:40', '', 306, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=308', 7, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (309, 1, '2013-09-22 18:30:00', '2013-09-22 18:30:00', '', 'IMiS/OCR Server', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '308-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:30:00', '2013-09-22 18:30:00', '', 308, 'http://imis.eberce.si/308-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (310, 1, '2013-09-22 18:30:36', '2013-09-22 18:30:36', '<blockquote><strong>IMiS/ARChive Server enables the storing of unlimited quantities of binary objects (scanned documents, files). It is used as an independent electronic archive for storing objects from various applications. The security of archived objects is provided by state-of-the-art algorithms for encrypting. Two additional security mechanisms are an audit trail for determining the activities on archived objects and the setting up of a secondary location for ensuring high availability of the archive system.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Storing Objects in the Electronic Archive Separately from the Application Solution</span>\r\nObjects are physically stored on IMiS/ARChive Server. While being saved, each object is assigned a unique ID, which is recorded in the logical document of the application solution (DMS, ERP, CRM, etc.). By selecting the relevant object from the logical document to be reviewed, the user uses the object ID to acquire that document from the archive server via the established connection and displays it in a suitable application viewer – in IMiS clients (Scan, View) or viewers of individual application solutions. By storing the objects in the electronic archive separately from the application solution, we achieve better efficiency and reduce the workload of the resources needed for the application solution to work.\r\nFor access to the archive server, IMiS clients (Scan, View) or IMiS/Storage Connector (server-server) are used.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Audit Trail for Recording Activities on Objects</span>\r\nThe audit trail helps determine the activities on archived objects. The system records all relevant data about who created, reviewed and changed the archived objects and when.\r\nThe audit trail is only accessible to authorized persons. The interface for viewing the audit trail offers a wide range of various queries. Recording of the audit trail can also be done in a remote system, reducing the possibility of unauthorized intervention into the audit trail by users with normally higher rights (system administrators).\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Linking to Various Applications</span>\r\nIMiS/ARChive Server can be linked to applications with the help of the IMiS/Storage Connector module, which provides the transfer of objects between the archive server and the application server. It uses a binary protocol for communicating with the archive server, which significantly speeds up communication, thus providing greater responsiveness and penetrability. Users of applications (ERP, DMS, CRM, etc.) display archived objects in the applications'' integrated viewers.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Security of Electronically Archived Objects</span>\r\nThe security of electronically archived objects is ensured by the state-of-the-art AES-256 algorithms for encrypting. Unique object identifiers (256-bit IDs) are encrypted in accordance with FIPS 197 specifications and prevent unauthorized access to and viewing of archived objects. Transport protocols are protected with relevant mechanisms (SSLv3, TLS, etc.). In security sensitive environments we enable the encrypting of the file system on the server, thus preventing access to unauthorized persons.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">High Availability Using One-Way/Two-Way Replication (Fail Over)</span>\r\nBy using replication and switching to a fail-over location we can establish the so-called backup centers, achieving a high availability (HA) of the archival system, while systems on separate locations also help us avoid data loss from potential natural disasters. Objects are periodically synchronized with other nodes in the cluster. In case of problems with any node in the cluster, clients are automatically redirected to others.', 'IMiS/ARChive Server', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'imisarchive-server', '', '', '2013-10-16 20:25:31', '2013-10-16 20:25:31', '', 306, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=310', 5, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (311, 1, '2013-09-22 18:30:36', '2013-09-22 18:30:36', '', 'IMiS/ARChive Server', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '310-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:30:36', '2013-09-22 18:30:36', '', 310, 'http://imis.eberce.si/310-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (312, 1, '2013-09-22 18:31:03', '2013-09-22 18:31:03', '<blockquote><strong>IMiS/BatchScan is a software product for scanning larger quantities of paper documents. During batch scanning, documents are created automatically on the basis of a distinguishing element (bar code, an empty sheet of paper, a certain number of pages). Different options for the scanning profile settings (paper size, resolution, color depth, brightness, sharpness, two-page scanning) enable the batch scanning of paper documents of varying readability and quality. The user interface is completely adapted to batch scanning, causing work to proceed fast and efficiently.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Bar Code for Distinguishing Documents</span>\r\nWe can achieve quick processing of larger quantities of documents by separating units within each batch. To separate one-page and multi-page documents, we most often use a bar code. In the process of batch scanning, IMiS/BatchScan searches for and recognizes bar codes on documents (on the whole page or only in a certain area) and enters them into the scanning results, along with other information (which can be used during recording into the information system).\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Simple Recording of Batch Scanned Documents\r\n</span>For faster recording of batch scanned documents, we first determine the metadata needed for further processing (compulsory, non-compulsory, textual, numeric, by date, etc.). These metadata, along with bar codes, form the data that can be used for automatic recording into other information systems. By marking the area of a document in which the data are located, we make it easier for the operator to enter the document metadata.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Advanced Work with Batch Scanned Documents\r\n</span>The general functionalities of software solutions for batch document scanning (enlarging, reducing, rotating) often do not meet the demands of advanced users. IMiS/BatchScan users can remove, insert, transfer, save and delete individual scanned documents or their pages from batch scanned documents. IP (image processing) filters are used to enhance scanned documents of lower quality. A hierarchical chart is formed for assigning names to documents. In settings, users can select the automatic removal of certain bar codes in the event of several bar codes on a single document, based on their values.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Use of a File System as the Source of Scanned Documents\r\n</span>If we need to batch scan in different locations (head office, branch offices), we can optimize scanning procedures by using only one IMiS/BatchScan product (lower total cost of ownership). We can import (individual documents or pages of) delivered scanned documents (stored on network drives, FTP transfer, CD, DVD, etc.) from the file system into IMiS/BatchScan, thus enabling further processing. The file system as the source of scanned documents can also be used when we have digitized content in different graphic formats and wish to unify the formats for better control over the quality of archived content before it is archived.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Automatic Archiving and Routing of Batch Scanned Documents\r\n</span>Paths to batch scanned documents, together with bar code information and potential metadata, are stored into an XML file. We wish to use these scanned documents and data in application solutions (ERP, DMS, CRM, etc.). Using IMiS/Avalanche or proprietary routing scripts we automatically route them into relevant notations of application solutions on the basis of bar codes and archive them on IMiS/ARChive Server.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'IMiS/BatchScan', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'imisbatchscan', '', '', '2013-10-16 20:13:07', '2013-10-16 20:13:07', '', 306, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=312', 2, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (313, 1, '2013-09-22 18:31:03', '2013-09-22 18:31:03', '', 'IMiS/BatchScan', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '312-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:31:03', '2013-09-22 18:31:03', '', 312, 'http://imis.eberce.si/312-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (314, 1, '2013-09-22 18:31:30', '2013-09-22 18:31:30', '<blockquote><strong>IMiS/Storage Connector is a software interface for object transfer (for scanned documents and files) between the application and archive servers. It functions in close connection to the IMiS/ARChive Server electronic archive and provides fast response times and high penetrability during the simultaneous exchange of larger quantities of objects. When an application demands the storing and reading of archived objects on the archive server, IMiS/Storage Connector transfers the objects between the application server and the IMiS/ARChive Server.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Simple Integration with Java and .NET Applications</span>\r\nIMiS/Storage Connector is designed in the .NET or Java technological environment and contains a wide range of program objects with a simple program interface (API). This enables a fast development of functionally advanced applications for access to the IMiS/ARChive Server. Two separate versions of IMiS/Storage Connector, one for the .NET and one for the Java environment, are available. A binary protocol is used to communicate with IMiS/ARChive Server, which greatly speeds up communication, thus providing higher responsiveness and penetrability. Users of DMS, ERP and CRM applications display the delivered objects in integrated viewers.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Use in SOAP Architecture</span>\r\nIMiS/Storage Connector is also used as a SOAP Service, which provides access to objects on IMiS/ARChive Server via a web server as a web service. Communication with IMiS/ARChive Server takes place via a binary protocol and with the application via a standardized SOAP protocol. We use it when we need support for the SOAP communication protocol (with regard to architecture or technology) for the storing and reading of objects on IMiS/ARChive Server, as well as for reading object properties (date created, date modified and other metadata). SOAP Service is currently available only for the Java environment.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Access to Objects Stored on Various Archive Servers</span>\r\nIf we have several IMiS/ARC archive servers in different locations, we can access objects stored on different archive servers from one application.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Security and High Availability of the System (HA)</span>\r\nIMiS/Storage Connector uses an encrypted communication protocol and algorithms for communication with various information systems, which prevents any potential eavesdroppers from unauthorized access to information. IMiS/Storage Connector can function even in very restrictive application environments with forbidden access to the file system, in which it uses RAM exclusively for its operations. The use of automatic switches between IMiS/ARChive Server nodes in the event of problems ensures high availability and consequently minimum outages of the archive system.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Advanced Functionalities</span>\r\nIMiS/Storage Connector ensures responsiveness and penetrability to heavily loaded application servers with advanced algorithms for session pooling. The object model provides all the necessary components for such an implementation to application solutions which need the streaming functionality. By using advanced caching algorithms, we reduce the need for communication between the application server and the electronic archive, thus contributing to faster operation of the system.', 'IMiS/Storage Connector', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'imisstorage-connector', '', '', '2013-10-16 20:22:45', '2013-10-16 20:22:45', '', 306, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=314', 8, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (315, 1, '2013-09-22 18:31:30', '2013-09-22 18:31:30', '', 'IMiS/Storage Connector', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '314-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:31:30', '2013-09-22 18:31:30', '', 314, 'http://imis.eberce.si/314-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (316, 1, '2013-09-22 18:32:49', '2013-09-22 18:32:49', '<blockquote><strong>IMiS/View is a software product for reviewing all major graphic file formats (TIFF, PDF, JPG, GIF, BMP, etc.). It is used to review all image files that are compressed with standard algorithms (CCITT G3/G4, LZW, JPEG, JPEG2000, JBIG, ZIP) and is adapted for reviewing multi-page documents.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Advanced Work with Documents</span>\r\nThe general functionalities of software products for document scanning (enlarging, reducing, rotating) often do not meet the demands of advanced users. IMiS/View users can add redactions and other annotations to documents (marking, emphasizing, overlapping, captioning, stamping, commenting). Annotations become part of the scanned document while being saved completely separately, which is made possible by the tool for merging with the original.\r\nIn addition, we can control user rights to changing the original, mark whole pages or individual parts, send documents directly via e-mail, etc. We can also add physically separate parts of the contents of other documents and merge them into one document.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Digital Signing of TIFF and PDF/A Documents</span>\r\nIMiS/View enables the digital signing of electronic documents in the TIFF and PDF/A format. Together with a digital certificate, the digital signature is used to verify the authenticity of electronic documents. It provides for the identification of the signee,\r\nthe unalterability of the signed content and enables the determination of the source of the signed content. Every unauthorized change to the document makes the digital signature invalid.\r\nThe documents can be signed parallel when there are several cosigners of the same source documents or sequentially in the case of a multi-level approval of documents. The digital signature and its graphic image, digital certificate data, the reason for signing and the commentary can be displayed on any page of the document or can remain hidden in the background.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Reviewing Directly from the Application Solution</span>\r\nUsing integration scripts, any application solution (ERP, DMS, CRM, etc.) can be closely linked to IMiS/View, making it possible for users to review documents directly from the application solution. This way, users do not have to use several applications, which affects the performance and quality of work done. When we view the scanned document, the application solution uses the saved ID to retrieve the relevant object from IMiS/ARChive Server and displays it in the IMiS/View viewer. The method of protecting the object ID is determined in the security scheme, which is taken in its entirety from the application solution.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Immediate Conversion of the Text of the Reviewed Document into Textual Form\r\n</span>IMiS/View++ is a software product that, in addition to all the functionalities of IMiS<sup>/</sup>View, also enables optical character recognition (OCR) of displayed documents, immediate conversion of displayed documents into a textual form and the enhancement of the quality of the document. IP (image processing) filters improve the processing of images (automatic alignment, rotation, noise reduction, automatic brightness adjustment, etc.). Using the PDF/A output format we can guarantee the long-term readability and authenticity of documents.', 'IMiS/View', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'imisview', '', '', '2013-10-16 20:17:50', '2013-10-16 20:17:50', '', 306, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=316', 6, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (317, 1, '2013-09-22 18:32:49', '2013-09-22 18:32:49', '', 'IMiS/View', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '316-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:32:49', '2013-09-22 18:32:49', '', 316, 'http://imis.eberce.si/316-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (318, 1, '2013-09-22 18:33:20', '2013-09-22 18:33:20', '<blockquote><strong>IMiS/Scan is a program module for scanning black and white and color documents and for reviewing them. It supports the standard formats for document scanning – multi-page TIFF and PDF/A. The online settings of the scanning profile (resolution, color depth, brightness, sharpness, sampling, two-page scanning) facilitate the efficient scanning of paper documents of various readabilities and quality levels.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Compression for Smaller Sizes and Faster Transfers of Scanned Objects</span>\r\nUsing standard compression algorithms (CCITT G3/G4, LZW, JPEG, JPEG2000, JBIG, ZIP) in different methods of document scanning (black and white, grayscale, color) we reduce the size of scanned documents, providing for faster transfers within the network and reducing the disk capacity needs. The size of a single-page scanned document is only 40–60Kb on average, while the size of a multi-page document increases linearly.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Digital Signing of TIFF and PDF/A Documents</span>\r\nElectronic documents in the TIFF and PDF/A format can be digitally signed by an IMiS client (View, Scan). Together with a digital certificate, the digital signature is used to verify the authenticity of electronic documents. It provides for the identification of the signee, the unalterability of the signed content and enables the determination of the source of the signed content. Every unauthorized change to the document makes the digital signature invalid.\r\nThe documents can be signed parallel when there are several cosigners of the same source documents or sequentially in the case of a multi-level approval of documents. The digital signature and its graphic image, digital certificate data, the reason for signing and the commentary can be displayed on any page of the document or can remain hidden in the background.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Advanced Work with Scanned Documents</span>\r\nThe general functionalities of software products for document scanning (enlarging, reducing, rotating) often do not meet the demands of advanced users. IMiS/Scan users can add redactions and other annotations to documents (marking, emphasizing, overlapping, captioning, stamping, commenting). Annotations become part of the scanned document while being saved completely separately, which is made possible by the tool for merging with the original.\r\nIn addition, we can control user rights to changing the original, mark whole pages or individual parts, send documents directly via e-mail, etc. While scanning, we can also merge several physically separate documents (e.g. a delivery note and an invoice) into one electronic document.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Scanning Directly from the Application Solution</span>\r\nUsing integration scripts, any application solution (ERP, DMS, CRM, etc.) can be closely linked to IMiS/Scan, making it possible for certain users to scan directly from the application solution. This way, users do not have to use several applications, which affects the performance and quality of work done. While being scanned, a document is automatically saved in the IMiS/ARC archive server. Only the scanned object ID is recorded into the relevant notation of the application solution in order not to burden the application itself. When we view the scanned document, the application solution uses the scanned object ID to acquire the relevant object from the archive server and displays it in the IMiS/Scan viewer. The method of protecting the object ID is determined in the security scheme, which is taken in its entirety from the application solution.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Using the TIFF and PDF/A Format for Long-Term Storage</span>\r\nDocuments intended for long-term storage in the electronic archive must be ensured readability and authenticity even after 5, 10 or more years. Using the output TIFF and PDF/A format, IMiS/Scan ensures the authenticity of documents for a longer period of time.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Immediate Conversion of the Text of a Scanned Document into Textual Form</span>\r\nIMiS/Scan++ is a software product that, in addition to all the functionalities of IMiS/Scan, also enables optical character recognition (OCR), immediate conversion of scanned documents into a textual form and quality enhancement. IP (image processing) filters improve the processing of images (automatic alignment, rotation, noise reduction, automatic brightness adjustment, erasing empty pages, etc.) and the detection of documents in the process of scanning, which in turn improves the readability of source documents of lower quality. Using the TIFF and PDF/A output format we can guarantee the long-term readability and authenticity of documents.', 'IMiS/Scan', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'imisscan', '', '', '2013-10-16 20:08:17', '2013-10-16 20:08:17', '', 306, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=318', 1, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (319, 1, '2013-09-22 18:33:20', '2013-09-22 18:33:20', '', 'IMiS/Scan', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '318-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-22 18:33:20', '2013-09-22 18:33:20', '', 318, 'http://imis.eberce.si/318-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (320, 1, '2013-09-22 18:33:48', '2013-09-22 18:33:48', '<blockquote><strong>IMiS/Avalanche enables the mass transfer of electronic documents (or digitized contents obtained by different means) and the automatic routing of documents and data to various information systems (ERP, DMS, CRM), including archiving on IMiS/ARChive Server.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source Data Capture from an Index File</span>\r\nData on scanned objects are most often captured from an XML file, which is the result of batch scanning with the IMiS/BatchScan product. IMiS/BatchScan stores paths to the batch scanned documents into an XML file, together with bar code information and potential metadata, which serves as input data for the processing in IMiS/Avalanche. An alternative for source data capture is the data that are the result of the generating of digitized contents and are equipped with a relevant bar code (external scanning, documents created in the ERP system, etc.)\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Automated or Interactive Method of Task Execution</span>\r\nIMiS/Avalanche can operate in automatic mode, on the basis of predefined intervals, and execute tasks. If greater control over execution time and the procedure itself is needed, the operator can execute tasks interactively via the user interface.\r\nExecution events are recorded in an event log, which can later be accessed to view the archiving procedure and document routing.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Use in the IBM Lotus Notes/Domino Environment</span>\r\nIMiS<sup>/</sup>Avalanche performs the archiving and routing of digitized content into relevant electronic folders of Lotus Notes documents, independently of the type of the Lotus Notes application solution. Using the paths to source files and potential metadata from the index file, IMiS/Avalanche first stores the source files to IMiS/ARChive Server and then writes the acquired IDs, along with potential metadata, into Lotus Notes documents in accordance with predetermined rules and predefined processes.\r\nThe digitized content is stored as objects to a physically completely separate IMiS/ARChive Server and NOT as attachments to Lotus Notes documents.\r\nAfter the digitized content is archived, we can optionally trigger adapted scripts, which enable users to execute specific applicative algorithms for the additional processing of documents after archiving.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Entry of Scanned Documents and Data into the SAP System</span>\r\nDuring automatic routing, IMiS/Avalanche acquires input data from the index file (bar codes, metadata, a link to source objects). Every object file (one-page or multi-page document or file) is assigned a unique ID upon being stored on the archive server.\r\nThe archived object ID and bar code data are entered into the SAP notations via the standardized SAP transactional RFC function ARCHIV_BARCODE_INSERT_RFC.\r\nAfter establishing a connection between the waiting SAP notation and the archived object, the document is accessible to users via the standardized ArchiveLink interface.\r\nWhen opening the SAP document, the user can select and view the scanned document (PDF/A, TIFF), depending on the settings, by using the menu function.\r\nAfter the user clicks on the attachment, SAP acquires the archived object from the electronic archive using its ID and displays it in the integrated SAP viewer.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Adapted Use with Plug-ins</span>\r\nFor the adapted use of IMiS/Avalanche we can make plug-ins that are completely adapted to the application logic of the system on which they are used (adapted routing of metadata, checking of metadata validity, entering of metadata into the standardized SAP environment, etc.). Plug-ins can support both the processing of the input data flow from the index file and entering it into various information systems (Lotus Notes, SAP).', 'IMiS/Avalanche', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'imisavalanche', '', '', '2013-10-16 20:15:46', '2013-10-16 20:15:46', '', 306, 'http://imis.eberce.si/?page_id=320', 3, 'page', '', 0);
