ator you can <a href="http://atros.editor.si/imis.si/en/solutions/migration-of-lndi-objects"><strong>Convert LN:DI (Lotus Notes Document Imaging) objects</strong></a> into standardized TIFF, PDF or PDF/A files and attach them back to your Notes documents. The process works on both embedded and/or LN:DI Mass Storage Server archived objects.</div>\r\n</div>', 'Solutions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '296-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-15 20:50:41', '2013-10-15 20:50:41', '', 296, 'http://imis.eberce.si/296-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (634, 1, '2013-10-17 21:10:41', '2013-10-17 21:10:41', '<blockquote><strong>The document management system enables effective management of paper documentation, a faster and higher quality flow of information, greater control over the implementation of processes, better insight into the cost effectiveness of business operations, the interconnection of information sources and conformity with the regulations in force. With the electronic implementation of document-intensive processes in a document management system, the processes are carried out significantly faster. Searching for documents is quick and easy; documents are not misplaced or lost; processing takes place faster. Employees can devote more of their attention to customers and value-added tasks and less to administration. </strong>\n<strong>By meeting the demands of customers more quickly, we are improving the level of services. Greater knowledge of the implementation of processes enables faster business decision-making.</strong></blockquote>\n<div>\n<div>Below is a list of the important features that we believe a <a title="Document management systems" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/document-management-systems/"><strong>DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT</strong></a> should offer:Individual and batch scanning enables a fast capture of documents that are immediately archived and thus made available to authorized users for the implementation of work processes.\n\nThe authenticity of electronic documents is confirmed by an electronic signature, which guarantees the authenticity of the document and the signee, the unalterability of the signed content and enables the determining of the origin of the signed content.\n\nData and documents from different sources are automatically routed to the document management system, which saves time on entering the record data and achieves greater transparency of the documents.\n\nElectronic support for processes (workflow) enables the optimization of working with documents, faster and greater access, a simple and organized method of working with business documentation, effective control over the implementation of business processes, precise tracking of work carried out, etc.\n\nOptical character recognition (OCR) of scanned documents is performed for all documents in full, thus ensuring a search through the full text of the documents. We can quickly find random parts of the text in documents, thus improving work productivity. We also save valuable time in the event of having to re-enter the text of received documents (retyping).\n\nThe existence of documents at a certain moment in time and their unalterability is confirmed with timestamping.\n\nSecure storing of a large number of objects, reliable operation, quick and easy search for objects and the option of storing them separately from applications are the key advantages of using an electronic document archive.\n\nFor the needs of mutual data exchange the document management system can be connected to other systems and applications.\n\nThe tool for process and data analysis is used to determine bottlenecks in the process and consequently optimize the implementation of the process. In order for its operation to be more responsive, the views and analyses are performed outside the document management system. Quality control over the implementation of processes can be a good foundation for the establishment of a more effective remuneration model.\n\n</div>\n</div>', 'Document management systems', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '302-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-10-17 21:10:41', '2013-10-17 21:10:41', '', 302, 'http://imis.eberce.si/302-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
