INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (743, 1, '2013-10-17 20:13:09', '2013-10-17 20:13:09', '<blockquote><strong>The document management system enables effective management of paper documentation, a faster and higher quality flow of information, greater control over the implementation of processes, better insight into the cost effectiveness of business operations, the interconnection of information sources and conformity with the regulations in force. With the electronic implementation of document-intensive processes in a document management system, the processes are carried out significantly faster. Searching for documents is quick and easy; documents are not misplaced or lost; processing takes place faster. Employees can devote more of their attention to customers and value-added tasks and less to administration. </strong>\r\n<strong>By meeting the demands of customers more quickly, we are improving the level of services. Greater knowledge of the implementation of processes enables faster business decision-making.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Below is a list of the important features that we believe a <a title="Document management systems" href="http://imis.eberce.si/en/solutions/document-management-systems/"><strong>DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT</strong></a> should offer:</div>\r\n<div>Individual and batch scanning enables a fast capture of documents that are immediately archived and thus made available to authorized users for the implementation of work processes.The authenticity of electronic documents is confirmed by an electronic signature, which guarantees the authenticity of the document and the signee, the unalterability of the signed content and enables the determining of the origin of the signed content.\r\n\r\nData and documents from different sources are automatically routed to the document management system, which saves time on entering the record data and achieves greater transparency of the documents.\r\n\r\nElectronic support for processes (workflow) enables the optimization of working with documents, faster and greater access, a simple and organized method of working with business documentation, effective control over the implementation of business processes, precise tracking of work carried out, etc.\r\n\r\nOptical character recognition (OCR) of scanned documents is performed for all documents in full, thus ensuring a search through the full text of the documents. We can quickly find random parts of the text in documents, thus improving work productivity. We also save valuable time in the event of having to re-enter the text of received documents (retyping).\r\n\r\nThe existence of documents at a certain moment in time and their unalterability is confirmed with timestamping.\r\n\r\nSecure storing of a large number of objects, reliable operation, quick and easy search for objects and the option of storing them separately from applications are the key advantages of using an electronic document archive.\r\n\r\nFor the needs of mutual data exchange the document management system can be connected to other systems and applications.\r\n\r\nThe tool for process and data analysis is used to determine bottlenecks in the process and consequently optimize the implementation of the process. In order for its operation to be more responsive, the views and analyses are performed outside the document management system. Quality control over the implementation of processes can be a good foundation for the establishment of a more effective remuneration model.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Document management systems', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-17 20:13:09', '2013-10-17 20:13:09', '', 302, 'http://imis.eberce.si/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (744, 1, '2013-10-17 20:14:55', '2013-10-17 20:14:55', '<blockquote><strong>IMiS®/ARChive Server is a safe, reliable and scalable archive system, intended for storing objects (of electronic source or digitized via the scanning process). Objects are stored in the structure of archive profiles. The archive system architecture is flexible and enables the setting up of a larger number of archive servers and the establishment of various roles in a hierarchy.</strong></blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Speed of operation (responsiveness, forwarding of archived objects) is independent of the archive size.The security of archived objects is provided with a unique, 256-bit encrypted identifier (ID), which is assigned to each archived object during the storage phase.\r\n\r\nIn environments where security is not provided by infrastructure (internet connections or exchange of highly delicate information), the internationally used and recognized AES-256 encryption standard is used to encrypt traffic between the server and the clients.\r\n\r\nFor the needs of storing objects separately from the application, the archive server is connected to various applications (DMS, ERP, CMS). For the application to access IMiS<sup>®</sup>/ARChive Server we use IMiS<sup>®</sup> clients (IMiS<sup>®</sup>/Scan, IMiS<sup>®</sup>/View) or the IMiS<sup>®</sup>/Storage Connector server.\r\n\r\nThe application''s security scheme defines the users that can access and view archived objects.\r\n\r\nThe audit trail, in accordance with the requirements of the legislation (Protection of Documents and Archives and Archival Institutions Act - ZVDAGA/ETZ), records all data on the implementation of operations on archived objects and is accessible only to users with special rights.\r\n\r\nThe high availability of the IMiS®/ARChive Server archive system is achieved by switching to replication and a fail-over location, thus setting up a secondary archive system in a remote location.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Electronic achive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '304-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-17 20:14:55', '2013-10-17 20:14:55', '', 304, 'http://imis.eberce.si/304-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
